text=(:Summary:Prerequisites for running the PmWiki wiki engine:)(:Audience: administrators (basic) :)%0aPrerequisites for running the PmWiki wiki engine:%0a# [[http://php.net/ | PHP]] 4.1 or later%0a** [[http://gophp5.org/ | PHP 5]] or later is recommended%0a# Some sort of webserver that can run PHP scripts.%0a%0aPmWiki has been reported to work with the following OS/webserver combinations:%0a* Apache 1.3 or 2.0, on roughly anything (Unix, Linux, Windows, and Mac OS/X)%0a** [[http://httpd.apache.org/ | Apache 2.2]] or later is recommended%0a* Microsoft Internet Information Server, on Windows%0a%0a* I got it to work on appWeb (a very small, php-enabled webserver) executing on a Linksys NSLU2 Network Storage Link device (runs Unslung 5.5 beta which is a Linux derivate for embedded systems). Still have to work out why file-uploads does not seem to work, however. --Hans-Göran Puke%0a%0a* PmWiki works very well on x86 Linux + [[http://www.litespeedtech.com/|LiteSpeedWeb Server]] Standard Edition  --Jeff Muday%0a%0aPmWiki has been reported not to work on:%0a* Mac OS before Mac OS X because there's no PHP available%0a%0aThe [[(Cookbook:)Standalone]] recipe provides a special, bare-bones webserver application that can be used to run PmWiki in places where another webserver isn't available.%0aPmWIki can also be run from a [[Cookbook:WikiOnAStick | USB drive]].
